Responsibilities:

  Manage corporate access for listed companies in Singapore and in the regional Stock Exchanges
  Organize and manage roadshows, marketing trips, corporate events &amp; conferences locally and in regional offices
  Build good relationships with the firm's clients and all stakeholders
  Research and analyze market trends, demographics, pricing schedules, competitor products, and other relevant information to form marketing strategies

Requirements:

  Previous corporate access/ institutional marketing experience with a Stockbroking firm / Investment Bank a plus
  Proven experience in organizing NDRs, Roadshows, Marketing trips, Conferences
  Diploma/Degree in Marketing, Mass Communications, Business Administration or equivalent
  Excellent written and verbal communication skills
  Strong project management, multitasking and decision-making skills
  Willingness and ability to travel
